An exponent tells us how many factors of the base we should multiply to find the value of an expression.

For example, we can take the power of a fraction like this:

$\begin{align}
\left(\maroonD{\dfrac34}\right)^\blueE{3} &= \maroonD{\dfrac34} \cdot \maroonD{\dfrac34} \cdot \maroonD{\dfrac34}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{3 \cdot 3 \cdot 3}{4 \cdot 4 \cdot 4}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{27}{64}
\end{align}$

