$\begin{align}
0.1^3 &= 0.1\cdot 0.1 \cdot 0.1
\\\\
&=0.001
\end{align}$

Since $0.1$ is one tenth, we can use fractions instead:

$\begin{align}
0.1^3 &= \dfrac{1}{10} \cdot \dfrac{1}{10} \cdot \dfrac{1}{10}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{1 \cdot 1 \cdot 1}{10 \cdot 10 \cdot 10}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{1{,}000}
\\\\
&=0.001 &&\gray{\text{(One thousandth)}}
\end{align}$

